45 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
46 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
47 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
48 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
49 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
50 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
51  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
52 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
53 #else
54 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
55 #endif
56 #endif
57 
58 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
59 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
60 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
61 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
62 #else
63 #error "unknown compiler"
64 #endif
65 
66 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
67 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
68 #else
69 #include <cstdio>
70 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
71  do { \
72  fputs(msg, stderr); \
73  DNNL_TRAP(); \
74  } while (0)
75 #endif

91 struct error : public std::exception {
92  dnnl_status_t status;
93  const char *message;
94 
99  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
100  : status(status), message(message) {}
101 
103  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
104 
110  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
111  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
112  }
113 };
114 
116 template <typename T>
117 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
118  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
119  const int size = (int)v.size();
120  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
121  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
122 }
124 
126 template <typename T>
127 struct handle_traits {};
128 
142 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
143 struct handle {
144 private:
145  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
146  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
147 
148 protected:
149  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
150  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
151 
152 public:
160  handle() = default;
161 
163  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
165  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
167  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
169  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
170 
176  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
177 
183  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
184  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
185  }
186 
192  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
193  T result = data_.get();
194  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
195  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
196  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
197  return result;
198  }
199 
204  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
205 
209  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
210 
217  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
218  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
219  }
220 
227  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
228 };

376 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
377  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
378  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
379  // returns a C type.
380  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
381  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
382  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
383  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
384  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
385 }

643 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
644  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
645  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
646  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
647  } \
648 \
649  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
650  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
651  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
652  } \
653 \
654  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
655  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
656  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
657  } \
658 \
659  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
660  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
661  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
662  return lhs; \
663  } \
664 \
665  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
666  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
667  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
668  return lhs; \
669  } \
670 \
671  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
672  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
673  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
674  return lhs; \
675  } \
676 \
677  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
678  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
679  }
680 
681 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
682 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

840 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
841  friend struct primitive;
842  friend struct reorder;
843 
845  enum class kind {
847  any = dnnl_any_engine,
849  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
851  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
852  };
853 
854  using handle::handle;
855 
858  engine() = default;
859 
864  static size_t get_count(kind akind) {
865  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(akind));
866  }
867 
873  engine(kind akind, size_t index) {
874  dnnl_engine_t engine;
875  error::wrap_c_api(
876  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(akind), index),
877  "could not create an engine");
878  reset(engine);
879  }
880 
881 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
882  engine(kind akind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
889  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
890  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(&c_engine, convert_to_c(akind),
891  device, context),
892  "could not create an engine");
893  reset(c_engine);
894  }
895 #endif
896 
901  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
902  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
903  error::wrap_c_api(
904  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
905  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
906  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
907  reset(c_engine, true);
908  }
909 
912  kind get_kind() const {
913  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
914  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
915  "could not get kind of an engine");
916  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
917  }
918 
919 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
920  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
923  cl_context context = nullptr;
924  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
925  "could not get an OpenCL context from an engine");
926  return context;
927  }
928 
931  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
932  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
933  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
934  "could not get an OpenCL device from an engine");
935  return device;
936  }
937 #endif

944  template <typename primitive_desc>
945  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
946  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
947  }
948 
949 private:
950  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind akind) {
951  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(akind);
952  }
953 
954  template <typename primitive_desc>
955  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
956  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
957  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
958  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
959  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
960  return engine(c_engine, true);
961  }
962 };

1043 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1044  using handle::handle;
1045 
1047  enum class flags : unsigned {
1050  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1052  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1054  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1056  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1057  };
1058 
1061  stream() = default;
1062 
1069  stream(const engine &aengine, flags aflags = flags::default_flags,
1070  const stream_attr &attr = stream_attr()) {
1071  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1072  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_v2(&stream, aengine.get(),
1073  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(aflags),
1074  attr.get(true)),
1075  "could not create a stream");
1076  reset(stream);
1077  }
1078 
1079 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1080  stream(const engine &aengine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1085  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1086  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, aengine.get(), queue),
1087  "could not create a stream");
1088  reset(stream);
1089  }
1090 
1093  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1094  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1095  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1096  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1097  return queue;
1098  }
1099 #endif
1100 
1103  stream &wait() {
1104  error::wrap_c_api(
1105  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1106  return *this;
1107  }
1108 };
1109 
1110 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(stream::flags)

1766  struct desc {
1767  friend struct memory;
1769  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1770 
1773  desc() : data() {}
1774 
1790  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag,
1791  bool allow_empty = false)
1792  : data() {
1793  validate_dims(adims);
1794  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1795  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
1796  convert_to_c(aformat_tag));
1797  if (!allow_empty)
1798  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1799  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
1800  "format tag");
1801  }
1802 
1818  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &strides,
1819  bool allow_empty = false)
1820  : data() {
1821  validate_dims(adims);
1822  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)adims.size());
1823  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1824  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
1825  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
1826  if (!allow_empty)
1827  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1828  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
1829  "strides");
1830  }
1831 
1835  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1836 
1839  //
1848  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets,
1849  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1850  validate_dims(adims, data.ndims);
1851  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
1852  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1853  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1854  &sub_md, &data, adims.data(), offsets.data());
1855  if (!allow_empty)
1856  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
1857  return desc(sub_md);
1858  }
1859 
1904  desc reshape(const dims &adims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1905  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(adims, 1);
1906  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1907  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
1908  &out_md, &data, (int)adims.size(), adims.data());
1909  if (!allow_empty)
1910  error::wrap_c_api(
1911  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1912  return desc(out_md);
1913  }
1914 
1951  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
1952  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1953  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
1954  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1955  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
1956  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
1957  if (!allow_empty)
1958  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1959  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
1960  return desc(out_md);
1961  }
1962 
1967  memory::dims dims() const {
1968  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
1969  }
1970 
1973  memory::data_type data_type() const {
1974  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
1975  }
1976 
1981  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1982 
1986  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1987 
1992  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1993  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1994  }
1995 
2000  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
2001 
2005  explicit operator bool() const { return data.ndims != 0; }
2006  };
2007 
2012  memory() = default;
2013 
2034  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine, void *handle) {
2035  dnnl_memory_t result;
2036  error::wrap_c_api(
2037  dnnl_memory_create(&result, &md.data, aengine.get(), handle),
2038  "could not create a memory object");
2039  reset(result);
2040  }
2041 
2048  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine)
2049  : memory(md, aengine, DNNL_MEMORY_ALLOCATE) {}
2050

2054  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_memory_desc(get(), &cdesc),
2055  "could not get a memory descriptor from a memory object");
2056  return desc(*cdesc);

2731  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
2732  zero_points[c] = c_zero_points[c];
2733  }

2913  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2914  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2915  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2916  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2917  query::exec_arg_md};
2918  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2919  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2920  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2921  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2922 
2923  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2924  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2925  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2926  }

3067  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
3068  "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3069  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);

3071 
3072 protected:
3076  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
3077  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
3078  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
3079  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");
3080  reset(new_pd);

3082 
3096  primitive_desc_base(
3097  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3098  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3099 
3111  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3112  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind aprop_kind)
3113  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, aprop_kind, aprop_kind) {}
3114 
3128  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3129  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3130  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3131  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3132  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3133 
3134  dnnl_status_t rc;
3135 
3136  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3137  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3138  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3139 
3140  // Check that primitive kind matches
3141  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3142  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3143  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3144  error::wrap_c_api(
3145  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3146  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3147  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3148  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3149 
3150  // Check that propagation kind matches
3151  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3152  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3153  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3154 
3155  // Something went wrong
3156  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3157  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3158  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3159  "descriptor");
3160 
3161  // Everything is fine
3162  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3163  || (rc == dnnl_success
3164  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3165  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3166  reset_with_clone(pd);
3167  return;
3168  }
3169 
3170  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3171  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3172  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3173  }
3174 
3175  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3176 };
3177

3197 
3215  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,
3216  const engine &dst_engine, const memory::desc &dst_md,
3217  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr(),
3218  bool allow_empty = false) {

3248  &src_md.data, src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
3249  dst.get_engine().get(), attr.get());
3250  if (!allow_empty)

3255  }

3325 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3326  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
3327  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
3328  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());
3329  for (const auto &s : mems)
3330  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
3331  return c_mems;

3522 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3523  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3524 
3525  primitive_desc() = default;
3526 
3549  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3550  const engine &aengine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3551  bool allow_empty = false)
3552  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3553  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3554  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3555  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, aengine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3556  if (!allow_empty)
3557  error::wrap_c_api(
3558  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3559  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3560  fetch_impl();
3561  }
3562 
3567  bool next_impl() {
3568  dnnl_status_t status
3569  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3570  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3571  error::wrap_c_api(
3572  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3573  fetch_impl();
3574  return true;
3575  }
3576 
3577 private:
3578  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3579  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3580  void fetch_impl() {
3581  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3582  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3583  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3584  : dnnl_out_of_memory,
3585  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3586  "descriptor iterator");
3587  reset(pd);
3588  }
3589 };

7239 
7240 protected:
7241  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7242 
7243  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7244  //
7245  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7246  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7247  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7248  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7249  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7250  //
7251  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7252  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7253  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7254  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7255  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7256  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7257  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7258  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7259  dnnl_status_t rc;
7260  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7261  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7262  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7263  "for an RNN primitive");
7264 
7265  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7266  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7267  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7268 
7269  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7270  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7271  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7272  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7273 
7274  if (!ok)
7275  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7276  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7277  "RNN primitive");
7278 
7279  reset_with_clone(pd);
7280  }
7281 };
7282

9607 struct resampling_forward : public primitive {
9609  struct desc {
9610  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
9611 
9627  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9628  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
9629  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9630  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9631  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), nullptr,
9632  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
9633  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9634  }
9635 
9647  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9648  const std::vector<float> &factors,
9649  const memory::desc &src_desc) {
9650  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
9651  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9652  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9653  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), &factors[0],
9654  &src_desc.data, nullptr),
9655  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9656  }
9657 
9674  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9675  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
9676  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
9677  if (!factors.empty())
9678  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
9679  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9680  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9681  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), factors.data(),
9682  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
9683  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9684  }
9685  };

10057 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &astream,
10058  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10059  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10060  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10061  for (const auto &a : args)
10062  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10063 
10064  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), astream.get(),
10065  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10066  "could not execute a primitive");
10067 }
